FINALLY, the Soweto 16 June students uprising will be captured on film.&nbsp;Sunday Sun can today reveal that talks with the affected families are at an advanced stage.According to sources close to the situation, the movie has three directors: award-winning Yizo Yizo director Tebogo Mahlatsi, Adze Ugah and Mickey Dube.The source said People&rsquo;s Poet Mzwakhe Mbuli is the brains behind the movie.The SunTeam saw part of the script showing that the movie will be shot in Gauteng.The storyline is state vs students, and the enemies are apartheid and Afrikaans.The source said Mzwakhe is also the movie&rsquo;s executive director.&ldquo;But he doesn&rsquo;t want to be in the limelight. He just wants to tell our history to the world,&rdquo; said the source.When called for comment, the People&rsquo;s Poet confirmed they were working on a movie.&ldquo;A lot has been said about many events of our past, but nothing was told about 16 June.&ldquo;This is not a comedy movie or fiction, it&rsquo;ll be a painful movie that talks about our history,&rdquo; he said.According to Mzwakhe, the movie will be emotional from start to finish.&ldquo;It&rsquo;ll be about fighting till the end. But it&rsquo;ll be the truth of what happened,&rdquo; said Mzwakhe.He said the reason for writing the movie was to educate the new generation about the events of that era.&ldquo;We want to tell our history through the movie and through South African voices.&ldquo;But we also want to tell our own story.&rdquo;Mzwakhe added that the search is already on for the cast and crew members.He said: &ldquo;It&rsquo;ll be a strictly South African cast and actors. There won&rsquo;t be any US actors.&rdquo;Without giving names, Mzwakhe admitted actors in the movie had already been identified.According to him, several actors and actresses would like to cast in lead roles.He said they have also started looking for people who would also play smaller roles in the movie.He told the People&rsquo;s Paper: &ldquo;It will have actors from Mzansi soapies.&ldquo;The movie is about this historic day in our country and is scheduled for release late next year or early 2019.&rdquo;